			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><a href="http://northwestengland.pm.org/">NWE.pm</a>[1] Hackday Part Trois[2]</p>
<p>Once again, and for the third year running as the subtitle crudely suggests, the <a href="http://northwestengland.pm.org/">North West England Perl Mongers</a> will be having a hackday to complete work on open source projects.</p>
<p>The hackday is traditionally held at the <a href="http://www.shadow.cat">Shadowcat Systems</a> offices in Lancaster, though physical attendance is not absolutely required as we will also be inviting virtual attendance to help work on projects. To gather as many people as possible we have chosen two dates in November to potentially hold the hackday and if you visit: <a href="http://www.doodle.com/7hrfz29pyx28usi5">http://www.doodle.com/7hrfz29pyx28usi5</a> you can vote on which one we use (either the 19th or the 26th).</p>
<p>This year we have chosen to do some major revamping of two community projects, <a href="http://www.presentingperl.org/">Presenting Perl</a> will have a host of features added and <a href="http://ironman.enlightenedperl.org/">ironman.enlightenedperl.org</a> will complete its transition to all.things.per.ly and have a major overhaul of features and look. You can join in the discussion of these on the irc channels #presentingperl, #epo-ironman and #northwestengland.pm on irc.perl.org and on the wiki at <a href="http://www.nwewiki.markkeating.me.uk/index.php?title=Main_Page">http://www.nwewiki.markkeating.me.uk/index.php?title=Main_Page</a>.</p>
<p>The projects will be managed by Ian &#8216;idn&#8217; Norton (Ironman) and Jess &#8216;castaway&#8217; Robinson (Presenting Perl) who will decide on features, technology and place people on tasks.</p>
<p>If you would like to attend this event, either physically or virtually then make sure to use <a href="http://www.doodle.com/7hrfz29pyx28usi5">http://www.doodle.com/7hrfz29pyx28usi5</a> before Friday 7th October so we can choose the best date to suit the most people to attend. Once we have chosen the date we will put up an event listing so you can choose physical/virtual attendance so we can get an idea of numbers (so <a href="http://www.shadow.cat">Shadowcat</a> can buy the appropriate number of snacks and pizzas)[3].</p>
<p>[1] North West England Perl Mongers</p>
<p>[2] How could there be only two, and jumping straight to four would just be obtuse.</p>
<p>[3] Snacks, pizzas etc. will only be provided for those in physical attendance, virtual attendees will have to find their own bites[4].</p>
<p>[4] Bites/Bytes geddit?[5]</p>
<p>[5] <strong>Groan.</strong></p>
]]></content:encoded>
